SYMPTOM_TEXT: I have reported adverse reaction to the first dose of vaccine, and was told to simply endure. I discussed those terrible adverse effects to two of the persons administering the second dose, and was assured with their theorizing that my second dose should have minimal side effects. By the time I go home I was in full blown headache, and immediately laid down in bed for an hour. Felling a bit better I got up to watch TV, and went downhill rapidly from there. The headache would not respond to acetaminophen. I also could not eat anything, so drank cranberry juice and V8. Evening sleep was awakened with sweaty pillow and sheets. I had to sleep with towels on bed and pillow. Next day was headache and overall malaise all day. I washed two acetaminophen at 4:30pm with orange juice. An hour later as I vomited the orange juice. That evening was the same as the previous. But by the time I finally got up at 8:30am that second day, I was feeling much better. I will never, ever accept a corona-virus vaccine ever again.
HISTORY: Possible history of alcohol abuse, but nothing current. Current health: Perfect.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I had strange vertigo like symptoms ~1 week after both of my vaccines.  The first time it happened, I actually didn't realize that it was from the vaccine.  The vertigo symptoms were especially happening when I would go from lying down in bed, to getting up/out of bed.  The room would spin and I would have to lie back down and then get up more slowly.  The vertigo would occasionally happen while I was standing.  The first time it lasted for ~1 week and I was starting to get worried but then it resolved, however the symptoms recurred ~1 week after my 2nd shot.  The exact same vertigo.  This time, I realized the connection and then looked back and resolved both symptoms occurred ~1 week after my vaccine.  The second time, the vertigo symptoms also lasted ~1 week.  However after the 2nd shot, I also had severe neck pain on the same side as my shot that radiated from my scapular area up to the the base of my skull.  This pain lasted for ~1-2 weeks, then both the vertigo and the neck pain resolved.

Received the vaccine at 10:40am on 3/24/2021 and felt normal. At 1:20pm anaphylaxis set in - experienced tingling then tightness in throat, tongue swelled, swallowing would cause me to choke and tongue would get stuck blocking air passage. Hyperventilating began as I could not get enough air into my lungs. For 15 minutes tried drinking water and laying down to help open airways. Breathing slightly eased for 2-4 minutes and then the anaphylaxis would spike again. This happened 3x getting worse,  I called my Primary Care Physician's office and was advised to go to the ER immediately. At 2:15pm I arrived at the ER and at 2:30pm I was given a 1mg shot of EPINEPHrine, and intravenous shots of diphenhydrAMINE, methylPREDNISolone, and famotidine along with oxygen. Anaphylaxis finally dissipated around 3:30pm and by 5pm I was breathing more normally. I was discharged at 7:00pm, and was feeling very energized. I was also given a prescription for an epipen incase I should have any further issues.  The next morning, 3/25/2021 I woke up after 5 hours of sleep feeling extremely energized. I had a virtual doctor's appointment with my allergist, Dr. at 12:00pm. My doctor was surprised at how well I seemed to be doing and we made arrangements to do further allergy tests in 2 weeks. We came to the conclusion that I am most likely allergic to POLYETHYLENE GLYCOL. This ingredient is also in a cold medicine that I was taking in January and I was experiencing minor anaphylaxis (which I thought was due to the extreme congestion I was experiencing with the cold). It is also an ingredient (aka PEG) in an eye cream that caused a severe eczema patch under my eye in January.   After my appt, at 1:30pm I went into anaphylaxis again. My throat got tingley and began to close, my tongue swelled and again was getting stuck in my throat when I attempted to swallow. I laid down and tried to get in deep breaths. My husband bought children's BENADRYL, which does not have polyethylene glycol in it, and gave me 15ml at 2:15pm. I reached out to my allergist, Dr. and updated him. He advised that I immediately take an additional 5ml of the BENADRYL. Dr. prescribed me 60mg/day Prednisone for 2 days followed by 40mg/day of Prednisone for 4 days, 40mg/day Famotidine for 2 weeks, 10mg/day antihistamine (I chose loratadine) for 2 weeks. Dr. also shared that I should have been prescribed steroids when I was discharged from the hospital, but my energetic state gave the impression I was OK. My manic energy was a result of the epinephrine, which had finally worn off 23 hours later, causing my body to begin the allergic reaction all over again.  The evening of 3/25/2021 (after the first dose of 60mg prednisone, 40mg famotidine, and 10mg loratadine) and all three meals on 3/26/2021 I experienced minor anaphylaxis when I began to eat. Tightness in throat throughout the meal and lasting an additional 20 minutes following the meal. My throat has reopened after each incident on 3/26/2021 and I was able to breathe normally again.
OTHER_MEDS: 5mg loratadine Ritual Prenatal Vitamin 1000mg turmeric  Probiotic
HISTORY: Hashimoto's Asthma Gluten Intolerance  Chronic Hives

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Within 2 hours of the shot, I got a headache and started feeling deathly ill.  I felt as if I was going to vomit and nothing I did helped.  My arm got a little red and sore a few hours after the injection.  Over the next few days my arm continued to get even more red & irritated as well as swelling some.  I have photographs of each phase of the irritation; if this is needed, I will gladly send them in to you all.  I had to stay out of work that whole weekend (2/26, 2/27, & 2/28) due to not being able to get out of bed.  I stayed in bed for the majority of the weekend sleeping and was not up moving around more than 8 hours the whole weekend.  Since I was still sick and having issues after so many days, the Medical Control Unit at my job (run by our Fire & Rescue Department) made me get tested on 3/1/21 to make sure it was not COVID.   Later that afternoon, the test came back as negative.  I still was feeling nauseated and fatigued even weeks after the shot.  I have stayed nauseated since then and have also been very tired still.
CUR_ILL: None other than the adverse effects I had from the first shot the month prior.
PRIOR_VAX: Adverse event from the first Moderna shot (report was already filed for that too).

Throat swelling, tongue tingling  Narrative: Code 99 called to the second floor auditorium where this simply  received her second coronavirus vaccine. Approximate 10 minutes later she  developed tightness around her neck and her tongue started to swell. No chest pain  or shortness of breath. No rash. Didn't have a problem with her first vaccine.  Epinephrine 0.3 mg 1M and Benadryl 50 mg 1M given. The patient started to feel  better. Tip of the tongue was slightly swollen and red. Patient spoke in normal  sentences. No stridor. Appears well and resting completely in the wheelchair.  Brought to the emergency department for further evaluation and observation. ED  provider note: 62 yo FEMALE w/ Wo multiple medication allergies p/w possible  allergic reaction. Pt recieved her second covid vaccination today @ approxately  1330 and reports nearly inmediate onset of sensation of "like a pill is stuck in  your flu-oat" and feeling like her throat was swelling. Then states that she  developed an abnormal sensation on the tip of her tongue described as tingling and  swelling. Denies any n/v, abdominal pain, sob or difficulty breathing. Pt received  0.3 mg of 1M epi as well as 50 mg of 1M benadryl. Pt observed in ED for 6hrs,She  was given steroids and Pepcid in the ER. She has an EpiPen at home due to an  allergy to bee stings. I told her that while a recurrence of her reaction is  she should pay close attention to any new or worsening symptoms and return to the  ER immediately for chest pain, shortness of breath, oral swelling, GI symptoms, or  any other new symptoms she develops that she is concerned about. She expressed  understanding of this plan. She was given a short course of steroids and  instructions for scheduled Benadryl for the next 24 hours.   Other Relevant History.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: After I was administered the shot. I was directed to a space designated for observation for patients after they receive the  vaccine. Within the first five minutes after I received my vaccine my mouth filled with an intense taste of metal and some numbness.  My body became very hot and almost heavy as I tried to stabilize myself to get help from the nurse. I was ushered to an area to lie down as I was going to faint. I was sweating profusely and about three minutes after laying there  the room turned cold and it felt such relief from the heat and sweating I felt such a short few minutes before. Both my hands became tingly and filled with the sensation of pins and needles. That symptom did not go away until about 15-20 mins later.  As I felt a little more strength and cooled body. I was able to sit up again. Not even five minutes later the heat and sweating came upon me again but this time for a shorter episode.  A light pins and needle feeling came about in my chest and tightness in the back of my neck.  I stayed in the observation room for one hour until the cycle of symptoms became more stabilized. The nurse was very confused by my symptom of metal taste in my mouth. One other patient had mentioned that but never got sick like I did.
OTHER_MEDS: No. I normally take omeprazole for acid reflux everyday but I did not take it on the morning of the vaccine
ALLERGIES: No allergies.  I just have asthma.

Patient received the first dose of the Moderna COVID-19 vaccine on Tuesday (03/23/2021) at 10 AM on her left arm. She did not feel the injection. No immediate symptoms after the injection. Before 1 PM, she developed itching at injection site and started to scratch her arm. Noticed ~5 visible bumps around injection site. She started to feel hotness on the injection site. Patient noticed that she also had hives on her right arm and one hive on her abdomen. She was on her way to work. Went to the pharmacist and told them about her hives. Was recommended to take cetirizine. Took cetirizine, hives were relieved but notes she was still feeling itchy. Had itching on legs, stomach, arms, face throughout the day. Patient worked from 1:30 - 11:00 PM. Did not do a lot of heavy lifting. Was working in her office and around the store. After her shift, patient still had itching. She also noticed swelling on her cheeks, from her outer lips towards her cheeks. Took diphenhydramine and went to sleep. On Wednesday (03/24) morning, she had red lips and lip swelling, as well as facial swelling. Has never had dermal fillers. She was feeling very itchy, especially on her face. Took diphenhydramine, swelling improved. Patient was taking diphenhydramine every 6 hours. Took one diphenhydramine yesterday 3/25. Has not been taking cetirizine. When she is taking diphenhydramine, patient does not have itching. Patient still feels some itching if she does not take diphenhydramine. No lip tingling. Ongoing itching and hives. I instructed her to take Xyzal tablets (which do NOT contain polyethylene glycol) instead of Zyrtec or Benadryl tablets.   She is scheduled for allergy testing in 2 weeks, if her urticaria has resolved.

I had a stage 1b malignant melanoma lesion removed from my right shoulder in 2014 and had completed all required follow-up. About a week after receiving the first dose (left arm), I noticed a small marble-sized lump in my right armpit. The lump continued to grow rapidly and I went to the doctor, after a biopsy and scans it was confirmed to be metastatic melanoma, most likely a recurrence from the 2014 melanoma. I received the second dose on 18 February (left arm) and noticed the lump in my right armpit grew much faster and I had a reaction (swollen nodes) in my left armpit as well. The melanoma is limited to my right armpit. We are reporting the event because of the timing of the melanoma recurrence in conjunction with the vaccination and because the National Institutes of Health is investigating the biopsy/pathology of the tumor in the right axilla as there are features they have never seen before in melanoma.

I woke up around 10 pm unable to open my eyes all the way.  I believe they were swollen nearly shut.  I could see a slit of light coming in from outside.  I couldn't move my left hand at all (left arm is where I received vaccination).  I held it up to the outside light, and it was swollen.  The light coming in from outside hurt my eyes.  I couldn't see enough to call for help.  Around 1:30 a.m., the swelling went down enough for me to open my eyes.  I have never seen them look so bloodshot.  It was scary.  I could move my hand again as well.  I spent next day in bed resting.   Monday, I noticed a small rash on my right shoulder.  I went to work and was there about 20 minutes before I started feeling hot and dizzy.  I went home and spent the day in bed.   I was able to go to work the next day, Tuesday, without problem.  One week after vaccination, the rash on my shoulder went away, but a small rash broke out on my right shin.  This one was deeper.  One week later, there are just a couple of small scabs left in the spot on my shin.  I feel my energy level is close to normal.

Patient a 41 y/o female with a history of HTN and anxiety presents to the Emergency Department with facial swelling in her left cheek that began today after she received her first dose of the Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine. She had a panic attack prior to getting vaccinated today. She was also feeling anxious while receiving the vaccine and states that she experienced a tingly sensation on the inside of her cheek as well as having a dry mouth. The patient denies trouble swallowing and eating, sinus pressure, shortness of breath, rashes, and dental issues. She notes that she has gone to the bathroom more frequently today but is not experiencing any diarrhea. Additionally, she has taken hydroxyzine for her symptoms. She is allergic to penicillin..  The onset was abrupt.  The course/duration of symptoms is constant.  Location: Left cheek. The character of symptoms is swelling.  The degree at present is minimal.  The exacerbating factor is none.  The relieving factor is none.  Risk factors consist of none. Prior episodes: none.  Therapy today: prescription medications including hydroxizine.  Associated symptoms: Dry mouth and tingly sensation on the inside of cheek. Associated injury none. She states she had a panic attack upon sitting down in the chair to receive her COVID shot in her left arm.  She had to take her anxiety medication there and then later in the day.  She states she felt as if the inside of her cheek was swollen and scratchy this made her very anxious and decided to come in to get checked out. She denies any hives any abdominal pain nausea vomiting shortness of breath chest pain or redness at the injection site.  She feels mildly improved from an anxiety standpoint now compared to the onset but still mildly anxious.  She has a very normal physical exam no neck tongue or lip swelling there is no redness at the injection site she has no hives abdomen is soft and tender or buccal mucosa is unremarkable ultimately patient reassured discussed it is important she get her 2nd COVID shot. SYMPTOM_TEXT: I have asthma that is primarily seasonal or exercise- induced.  About 2 days after the vaccination,  I experienced asthma symptoms that lasted for about 5 days. I had shortness of breath,  wheezing,  resulting lightheadedness, and some dry coughing. Symptoms were worst first thing in the morning and at night. I am still experiencing some lingering difficulty breathing 10 days out from the vaccine, but no wheezing.   It is very likely that I had COVID-19 in early February 2020, before testing was available in the here (My coworker returned from abroad very ill; another coworker and I became sick shortly after,  and she lost her sense of taste and smell. I experienced low grade fever,  intense nausea,  diarrhea,  shortness of breath,  and extreme fatigue.  The fatigue lasted for about one month.) Following this illness,  I saw a sharp increase in my asthma symptoms for about 6-7 months,  which gradually tapered off. Again, there was no other trigger for these symptoms such as exercise or humidity. It seems likely that I contracted COVID-19, which damaged my lungs in some way,  and that the vaccine has resulted in irritating or "re-activating" that damage at a lesser intensity.

Pfizer COVID-19 Vaccine EUA  Patient presents 3/23/21 for medical monitoring of syncopal episode s/p COVID - 19 vaccine # 2.  Lowered to the floor by vaccine staff.  Patient reports symptoms of weakness, other wise states she ""feels fine"". Two additional syncopal episodes witnessed by myself when patient attempts to change position.  Past medical history is significant for mild persistent allergic asthma, pre-diabetes, OSA, obesity and BPPV.  Patient reports history of same reaction s/p previous vaccine.  At a approximately 0837 patient was noted to have a worsening rash present to her face.  EpiPen administered via left lateral thigh at 0838.  EMS called to transport patient the ED for further evaluation.    Treatment administered: epipen (lot 0FM406, exp 02/22) left lateral thigh at 0838.    Upon arrival to the ED, patient's temperature is 98.8� F, heart rate 92-103, respiratory rate 30, saturating 99% on room air with blood pressure 164/91.  The patient's laboratory studies were largely unremarkable.  While in the ED, the nurse was getting ready to get the patient up to the commode when the patient started to ""not feel right again.""  She asked her to administer the medications for allergic reaction and reports wall the 2nd medication was being infused, she felt paralyzed and unable to talk, although she was able to hear everything and was aware, she was unable to move or speak for a short amount of time.  CT head with completed at this time and showed no acute intracranial findings.  Chest x-ray unremarkable.  EKG showed normal sinus rhythm with sinus arrhythmia, heart rate 80 and prolonged QT at 470.  The patient was administered Solu-Medrol 125 mg IV, Pepcid 20 mg IV, Benadryl 50 mg IV, normal saline 1 L IV.  Pt was admitted to hospital for observation.    The patient was seen on the unit laying in bed with her husband at the bedside.  She reports that she is feeling slightly better and hungry and has never felt at paralyzed/unable to speak feeling before and is very nervous about this.  She was wondering if she had a seizure, although she reports feeling aware the entire time and did not lose bowel or bladder function. We discussed that that is not typical for a seizure, but even if we did an EEG at this time, it would not be able to tell us what occurred in the past.  We discussed continue the Benadryl, Pepcid, and IV steroids for today and likely decreasing them tomorrow. We discussed the workup of syncopal episodes as well. The patient and her husband were agreeable to this plan.    Patient was discharged from the hospital on 03/24/2021 in a stable medical condition.  Patient was instructed to follow-up with her PCP in 1 week.

Had only a sore arm after 1st Moderna shot.  Received 2nd Moderna shot on 3/21/21 AM.  Sore arm began at ~8h, chills began ~11 h, achiness & headache ~14 h, shooting pains (mostly to head) began ~17 h ... these side effects continued through the day after vaccination.  After 48 h, the chills/fever were gone, but the head & muscle aches continued (tho diminished), so I took 1 Advil and felt much better that night.  But on both 3/24 and 3/26, I experienced severe vertigo/dizziness/room spinning on awakening and for a couple hours longer; this was accompanied by nausea, headache, some hot flashes and mild chills.  In both instances, the vertigo gradually eased during the day and I felt considerably better by evening.  The dizziness is very unpleasant and disruptive, so I'm hoping it doesn't return; it?s too soon to know if it will, but I will see my PCP if the problem persists.  Of course, I can?t be sure the dizziness was caused by the vaccine, but it seems likely.    I?ve had many vaccines and tolerated almost all of them very well.  But I had a strong reaction to Shingrix in August, 2019 ? had a huge, red, hot swelling of my arm around the injection site, and very bad chills, fever, muscle aches, head ache (but no vertigo).  Spent ~2.5 days in bed.

Patient was found deceased in his own home on Monday, March 15, 2021.  He was found on the floor in a sitting position with three fingers of his right hand on his right carotid.  It appeared that he was getting ready for church, which was a routine event.  Although patient was a diabetic, he never had episodes that were life threatening, and was always able to manage to remediate with insulin or food.  Patient last spoke to a neighbor at 2:30 a.m. on Sunday, March 14th, who said he appeared to be just fine and they scheduled a date with their dogs on Sunday afternoon.  A sheet of instructions found on the kitchen counter at the home informed us that he had a COVID vaccine at the VA Hospital on Wednesday, March 10th.  He was documenting side-effects of very sore  right arm and low blood sugars.  that was unusual because if he was able to manage he wouldn't have noted it.  It was apparent that something sudden happened such that he was unable to get to help and his heart rate must have been of concern.  We believe that patient suffered  onset of some sort of cardiac event, blood clot, high heart rate, or heart attack, that was associated with the vaccine on Wednesday and 4 days later he was suddenly gone, unable to call for help (he has family close by in this community).  We want healthcare providers and individuals to be able to make informed decisions about giving/taking the vaccine when there is another health issue  such as diabetes to consider.  We lost a brother, a father, a friend and a dedicated veteran unnecessarily.
LAB_DATA: No autopsy was performed since this was considered to not be a suspicious event

Pfizer COVID-19 EUA Vaccine  Pt received first COVID vaccine 2/25/21. Tested positive for COVID late February. Reported to ED 3/5/21 with near syncope. Patient was seen emergency department laying in bed. The patient had a noticeable scalp laceration to posterior parietal area.  After being symptomatic with COVID-19 for a few days, the patient reports getting up at 5:00 a.m. to use the bathroom, feeling lightheaded, then ended up on the floor, she reports sitting on the floor and then hit her head at some point, but was not entirely sure of this timeline.  She states she ended up moving to the living room when she noticed that her head was bleeding a lot and her fiance called 911. She reports a history of syncopal episode in 2001 when she had influenza and apparently the story was much the same as this time, but she actually lost consciousness in 2001. Admitted to observation.    3/7: 73-year-old female recent COVID-19 infection admitted on 03/05/2021 for an episode of syncope probably secondary to bradycardia versus volume depletion.  Paramedic on arrival at home reported bradycardia with heart rate in the 30s but has been normal since admission. The CT angiogram of the chest done at the emergency room showed bilateral infiltrates compatible with recent COVID-19 infection.  No PE.  However patient has no respiratory symptoms and O2 saturation is perfectly normal.  Urinalysis was suggestive of infection and subsequent culture was positive for E coli and it is pansensitive.    She was admitted to hospital for overnight observation.  She was commenced on IV Rocephin and azithromycin.  The EP cardiologist was consulted and she recommended and echocardiogram and it revealed mild global hypokinesis with LVEF of 45-50% but patient denied any prior history of cardiac problem.   On re-evaluation this morning the vital signs remains normal.  Patient has not had any episode of bradycardia since she presented to the emergency room.  She will be discharged home follow up with the EP cardiologist for further evaluation. Patient does not need outpatient oral antibiotics as IV Rocephin for 3 days should be adequate for uncomplicated UTI.

I received my vaccine on the 25th at 8:50 a.m.  At 4:00 a.m. on the 26th, I woke up with a pain in my chest that wasn't too bad, and a slight headache. I got up and went to the bathroom and took my temperature. It was 101.9. I went back to bed and the pain in my chest felt like a spasm at the base of my esophagus. It would come and go and I thought it might be indigestion or something but it coincided with when my temperature started. I had woken up a few times before 4:00 and felt chilled but had taken my temp  and I didn't have any. Over the course of the next few hours, the pain got more and more intense to the point my husband felt we should go to the emergency room. When it would be in my chest area, it was excruciating. It would alternate between the center of my chest and then would be in the center of my back between my shoulder blades. I took five or six Tums over this period of time. I took two Tylenol at around 5:30 a.m.  The episodes lasted several minutes, would ease a little and then start up again. My temp started to come down around 6:00 but was still 100.1.  The pain in my chest felt like a spasm type pain, but when it would go to my back, that was a fairly constant pain. I finally agreed to go to the emergency room and my husband helped me get dressed. This was about 6:30 a.m.  Shortly after that, the episodes started spreading out to where they weren't as long or frequent. About 7:45 a.m. they had eased up completely, and I took my temp again at that time, and it was completely normal. We did not end up going to the emergency room.  The pain did not come back for the rest of the day.
OTHER_MEDS: Tums, multivitamin, calcium with vitamin D

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 45 minutes after injection I felt very strange, this increased to a point where I felt as if I were on drugs. I never take drugs, I was fortunate that my boyfriend had driven me there as I was really out of it. I felt like my brain was disconnected and expanded at the same time. This unconnected sensation went on for hours. I had to stay home as I was so spaced out. At night I lay in bed singing songs that had no meaning and then laughing!  What!  The next day I was still not properly connected and spaced out. I could work instinctively but the more rational part of my brain was not working. A week on I still feel a disconnection in the center of my brain.  The second day I had a slight fever, and by the 4 th day I had diarreha.  I am still not properly 'right'.  I am deeply concerned about getting a second shot, I don't want some kind of permanent brain disfunction.  I want you to know that this is not in any way normal for me. I don;t take hallucinogens, a barely even take aspirin.  My boyfriend thought it was hysterical because he had never seen me like that before. I was babbling on about my internal (now its going into my brain, now its in my feet) and external (look at the river, oh its a house, we're on the road)experiences not able to connect to him at all.   So as you can imagine I am in a quandary about the second shot. I just don't know what to do, and if I have the never to get it. I'm schedule for April 14th.

I received the Johnson & Johnson COVID-19 vaccine at 8:30AM on Friday, March 26. The only symptoms I experienced until that evening were mild soreness at the injection site, mild stiffness/soreness in my left arm and my neck, and mild body aches. At 6:00PM that day, I was driving and experienced sudden-onset nausea and dizziness. I experienced tunnel vision and my vision began to black out. I was able to pull off the road and began retching and dry heaving. I also experienced tingling/numbness in my lips and then in my right hand, each of which lasted for about a minute. The nausea lasted for 5-10 minutes, after which it dissipated and I started experiencing chills. After returning home, around 9:30PM I experienced a severe headache and a return of sudden-onset nausea. I also experienced tingling/numbness in my right hand again, which disappeared after about 5 minutes. I retched and dry heaved again, and I took two Advil. SYMPTOM_TEXT: Right ear pain started on the Wednesday afternoon, two days after Vaccine shot. By Friday evening the ear pain was intense and it had moved below the ear to lymphnode area. Saturday, his ear was really swollen and red. He went to the Urgent Care and they prescribed an antibiotic Cephalexin thinking it could be some sort of ear infection or insect bite. Sunday morning he woke up with his face droopy. We tried to get an appt. with Urgent Care, but they sent us to the ER. The ER did a physical assessment and concluded he had an ear infection and Bells Palsy. The prescribed another antibiotic Doxycycline, an antiviral Famciclovir and a steroid of prednisone. By Monday he was extremely nauseas and had started having vertigo. We went to Urgent Care and they prescribed him Ondansetron for nausea and made the assessment that he had Shingles in his ear. We saw PCP on Wednesday and he assessed that this was a zoster ear infection causing facial paralysis and vertigo, also known as a rare condition called Ramsay Hunt Syndrome and that it was most likely attributed to his Covid vaccine shot and not to get the second vaccine shot. The Dr. took him off the antibiotics and put him on a higher dose of prednisone, a different antiviral (valacyclovir) and Meclizine for vertigo symptoms. He sent referrals for Neurology, ENT and Eye Dr. He saw the Neurologist that Friday and he concurred Ramsay Hunt Syndrome, most likley from Covid Vaccine and do not get the second vaccine shot. The neurologist referred him to Physical Therapy to treat his vestibular issues. He ordered an MRI and some blood work. We are still waiting for the results. We saw an ENT an he had him have a hearing test which showed moderate high frequency hearing loss. The ENT prescribed Gabapentin for the ear and face pain. He started to see a physical therapist this week, he had his MRI on Wednesday and we see the ENT again on Monday. He has no improvement yet, other than the nausea has subsided.
LAB_DATA: physical assessment, MRI (no results yet), bloodwork (no results yet), hearing test - moderate high frequency hearing loss

SYMPTOM_TEXT: About 45 minutes after the vaccination I felt like my body was buzzing.  This eventually rose upward until the buzzing sensation concentrated on the top of my head, at which point I developed an excruciatingly painful headache.  About six hours after the vaccine, I started having a fever that eventually was so intense that I felt like my eyelids were going to peel off.  Then I started having chills.  I was so cold when I had the chills that I shook like someone having convulsions.  When I felt hot, I felt like my eyelids would peel off.  I drank some water at one point and felt like I'd vomit.  Then, a bit later, I felt like I was going to have diarrhea.  About eight-ten hours after the shot, it felt some my tendons were being twisted so that my bones were being ground together at the joints.  Then I started having muscle pain.  I have a very high pain tolerance.  This was ungodly.  I felt like I was being tortured.  This lasted 36 hours.  Then my hair started falling out.  The week before the vaccine was the snow storm.  I had no power for a couple days and no usable water for about five days.  I think that my unfortunate telogen effluvium is the result of extreme stress during the storm followed by extreme stress due to the vaccine.  However, given that I had beautiful. long, abundant curly hair, this is obviously not a felicitous event.  On 3/11, my levator scapula and rhomboid on the left side (shot side) started feeling hot and very hard.  Then my posterior and medial deltoid and triceps muscles started rippling (visibly).  Then the injection site swelled up so that it looked like I had a large grain of rice sticking out from my arm.  Then the anti tragus of my left ear swelled and turned red.  I developed floaters in my left eye.  This lasted for about 48 hours.  My hair, which had stopped falling out, started shedding again.   I have lost about 55% of my hair at this point.  My arm never really stopped hurting.  I have gotten my second shot (3/25) and am at present working through my adverse events after it, but will wait for a couple weeks before reporting them.  I don't know if I'll have "Moderna arm" again, so once the two-week mark passes, I'll report.  As best I know, I have never been exposed to COVID19, so the idea that I had such a reaction because of that is not relevant.
OTHER_MEDS: Vitamin D3; B Complex; Vitamin C

At 5pm on 02/27/2021 I felt faint, checked pulse manually and with an Apple Watch.  Pulse was 145.  No chest pain, dyspnea or other symptoms.   Neither pulse rate nor symptoms changed over the subsequent 36 hours.  On March 1, 2021 I went to a local Emergency Department for evaluation.
LAB_DATA: EKG in the Emergency Department was read as Atrial Flutter with no other abnormalities.  Physical exam, CXR and standard blood work (CBC,CHEM 6 panel was normal except for slightly elevated troponin 0.26 (subsequent troponin measurements trended down).  I was admitted for observation after IV heparin and diltiazem were started in the Emergency Department.   On March 2 at ~ 2pm I was cardioverted with a single shock of 200J which restored normal sinus rhythm.  I had a MUGA scan the following day which was read as normal.  I was then discharged on ASA 81mg daily and Eliquis 5mg. po bid.  I have been in a normal sinus rhythm as 55-60 since my discharge with no reoccurrence of this arrhythmia.  To my knowledge I have never had an arrhythmia diagnosed previously.

I have degenerative back disease and my doctor had given me a prednisone dose pack for me to have on hand if the pain got out of hand.  When I started having numbness on the right side of my head (especially my eye lid, upper teeth on the right side, right cheek, ear and behind the ear), I first just used prednisone cream, and found it to help, but not fully.   After reading that others had bells palsy after having the shot, and my symptoms seemed similar to bells palsy, I looked up the treatment for bells palsy to be prednisone dose pack.  Since I had one on hand, and online stated it would be best to start immediately to avoid any long term effects, I took the first dose on Friday, March 26th.  Within 20 minutes my tingling started to subside.  I still am experiencing numbness on the right side of my face, but it is significantly reduced, I would say approximately 90% better.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: About 5 hours after my vaccine I had already been asleep for around 30 minutes when I was startled awake by my own rapid heartbeat, it was beating so fast and hard that I could hear it and it woke me up. I reviewed my literature about the vaccine I received at the pharmacy and saw this reaction could be due to an allergic reaction but as an uninsured person I had to just wait it out to see if it would go away. I drank a lot of water and started developing a headache but my heart rate finally slowed down enough that I was no longer alarmed, but it was still faster than usual. I went back to sleep around 2am only to awake once again around 5am because I had begun to experience the worst body aches I?ve ever felt as well as nausea and a pounding headache. I live on a semi truck with no bathroom so my fianc� had to take me to my parents house so I would have access to a bathroom. I took ibuprofen and Tylenol for my pain and took 6 showers in 24 hours just to soothe my body aches. It felt worse than any flu I?ve ever had (I received the flu vaccine back in January if that matters). I was extremely ill and had no appetite and pretty much just slept and cried for about 36 hours total, but yesterday afternoon I finally felt a little better although still experiencing a terrible headache. Today I woke up feeling completely fine. I just wanted to report my side effects.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Started with lethargy and hot flashes, followed by extreme shortness of breath, difficulty speaking and holding up my head and keeping my eyes open. Then trembling. The local nurse at the vaccination sight reported high blood pressure, rapid pulse and seemingly extremely low blood sugar. I didn?t go to the ER because my supervisor agreed to take me home since we were volunteering at the sight prior to me receiving the vaccine. I had to keep eating every hour or so due to blood sugar seeming very low. Shortness of breath continued. Pulse rate still high as I could sleep with my head down due to racing pulse in my head. Later that night I had small bumps on my arms with no itch. Then I had extreme fatigue and muscle fatigue. I kept experiencing extreme episodes of hot flashes. I woke up in the middle of the night with a headache and uncomfortable hot flashes. I drank 100% juice and ate a few goldfish. I had mild nausea and food aversions. The next day the bumps were gone. I went to work but was sent home. I was told I should have gone to the ER but I don?t have insurance. Once home, I went through 5 hours of extreme chills unlike anything I have ever experienced. I had to cross my arms over my chest and stack on blankets to regulate. If I moved my arms for more than five minutes or pulled the blanket down, I began uncontrollably trembling. I still had trouble regulating my blood sugar on day two. It?s day three and no bumps and no chills. Less muscle fatigue as well. I am still pretty exhausted and tire easy when doing things. I did experience the common soreness in the muscle the vaccination was administered, but I figure that is normal.  I am hopeful that I am improving and out of the danger zone. I took Garden of Life Elderberry with added nutrients last night and today I took my normal detox probiotic. I have been pushing fluids and have broken my intermittent fasting to try and keep my blood sugar up. I feel like my system is finally regulating and now I just have lingering exhaustion from the events that took place.
LAB_DATA: I did not go to the doctor due to lack of insurance.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I am an internal medicine provider and have an 18-year h/o rheumatoid arthritis that had been well-controlled for years allowing me to stop treatment with MTX/leucovorin 3 years ago.   On 2/28/021 I developed pain, erythema, warmth and swelling at the 4th MCP in my L hand which persisted for several days.  I contacted my rheumatologist, and saw him on 03/04.  Since this was my first episode of inflammation in years, we elected to treat it conservatively with naproxen OTC.  My symptoms resolved after several days, but then I had successive episodes of pain, erythema, warmth and swelling in my R 5th MCP, R ankle, L 5th TMT, L 5th MCP, L knee and R wrist over the next 3 weeks--- in the pattern of palindromic rheumatism similar to that my symptoms had first began 18 years ago.  Given the number and severity of these episodes, doctor recommended treatment with prednisone 10mg PO qdaily for 30 days and restarting MTX 15mg (six 2.5mg tabs) PO qweekly  and folate 1mg PO qdaily.

FYI- when I had COVID-19 in November 2020 I lost my taste and smell and had sinus-infection symptoms. I may have noticed some slight changes in tastes prior to February 25th, but I don't think so.  On this particular night I had a Sprite- it tasted very bad- like cleanser and horseradish and floral.  I started to have other things taste like this including my toothpaste, A1 steak sauce.  My family tasted these items too and said they were fine.  At one meal my family said the mushrooms didn't taste fresh and that they might be expired, but I couldn't taste the difference. I messaged my doctor who said it was okay to get the second shot.  My taste-senses were still out of whack when I received the second dose on Mar 14. Within about 18 hours of the second vaccine shot I had a bad headache and a low-grade fever of about 101 degrees. Although trying to manage the pain with 2X 500 mg of acetaminophen every 6 hours, I was throwing up, pacing, rocking and becoming so weary of how was I going to get through this.  A fever of 101.5 started sometime on Sunday and fluctuated but was no higher than 101.7.  A heating pad  helped to ease the pain and I was able to get some sleep until the flare up would start all over again.  This continued throughout the day for 17 hours.   By Monday , March 22, morning the intense pain was gone and my body was recouping.  My stomach was achey from either the intense pain or the vomiting.  I continured to run a fever of 101.  until Tuesday afternoon, March 23.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Same evening of vaccine injection 3/24 - chills and severe headache and extreme fatigue.   Overnight - nausea, vomiting and fever 102.6.  Next morning 3/25, woke up and tried to get out of bed.  Legs were so weak they gave out and I fell out of bed on the floor.   I had no strength to get back up to get on the bed.  My wife could not lift me, so she called 911 for a "lift assist".  Paramedics were told I received the 2nd dose of the Covid vaccine the day before, so they picked me up off of the floor and put me back in bed.  They took my vitals - blood pressure was 116/73 and temperature was still 102.6.  Paramedics offered to take me to the hospital but I refused.  Paramedics told my wife that if my breathing became labored, she should get me to the ER or call 911 again.    I was not able to get out of bed the whole day on Thursday 3/25, because I was so weak I could not stand up, and I also had body aches and had to use a urinal because I could not walk to the bathroom.  My wife gave me Tylenol and the fever finally broke late evening of Thursday 3/25 and I started to feel a little bit better.  I had not eaten all day, but my wife made sure I stayed hydrated with water.  On Friday morning 3/26 I was able to sit up on the side of the bed, and I was able to walk with the assistance of a cane to the bathroom.  Extreme fatigue affected me all day Friday, but I did feel better.  Fever did not come back after it broke.  Saturday 3/27 - still experiencing extreme fatigue, but feel better overall.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: This was my second dose of the Pfizer/BioNTech COVID-19 vaccine. I took some notes during my waiting time following my injection similar to my first dose. Information from my last report can be found using Temporary VAERS E-Report No: 334845. Of note, I did prepare for my second dose by taking Benadryl 50 mg and Airborne Immune-Boost supplements the night before my second dose, so my symptoms were not as severe as last time.  6 minutes: Mild tingling around tongue. This time all around the edges of my tongue, but a lot less bothersome than the first dose. 8 minutes: Weird. Slight itchiness under left half of tongue. Still very mild but less concerning than first dose itchiness on the left and right sides of my tongue. 18 minutes: Itchy on right side slightly, only side noticeable. 20 minutes: Mild warm feeling on left side of top of my throat. Less bothersome than time. 26 minutes: Left throat warm ness resolved, but transitioned to right side of top of my throat. 31 minute: Throat warmness overall resolved, but slightly itchy on edge of right side of my tongue. 37 minutes: Top of throat on right feels weird but not itchy. Warm maybe? 39 minutes: Weird feeling on right side of throat resolved.  Symptoms more or less resolved the rest of the day, especially after second dose of Flonase @ 9:00 am.  14 hours later: About to go to bed. Feeling fatigued, similar to my first dose after working out. Took airborne and two Benadryl (25 mg each) before sleeping.  24 hours later: 03/27/2021, feeling more fatigued, groggy, mild headache (mostly at back of my head), and muscle aches around my body.  25 hours later: Groggy feeling and fatigue resolved. Possibly due to Benadryl or vaccine?  32 hours later: Majority of muscle aches resolved. Headache also resolved. Feeling mostly soreness at this point.  Drank Airborne @ 10:00 am and 4:00 pm. In between drank plenty of fluids (water, cranberry juice, apple juice, milk). No fever or chills.
OTHER_MEDS: -Airborne x2 effervescent tablet (first @ 11:00 pm on 03/25/2021 and second @ 7:00 am on 03/26/2021) -Benadryl (took 2 tablets of 25 mg tablets @ 11:00 pm on 03/25/2021) -Flonase (took spray in both nostrils @ 7:00 am)
PRIOR_VAX: Pfizer/BioNTech COVID-19 Vaccine 1st dose

Received vaccine in left shoulder at 9:30 AM Weds.  By about 5:30 PM on Weds, I noticed that I felt tired and had muscle soreness in my left shoulder.  By about 6:30, I felt feverish, chilled, and increasingly tired, noticed twinges of pain with movement of my right elbow.  Felt increasingly achy in back, legs, hip joints and muscles, headache, and continued to feel fever/chills until about 11:30 PM Weds, when I took 2 ibuprofen and fell asleep.  Woke at about 7:00 AM Thurs, still felt tired/fever/chills/body aches and soreness at injection site.  Also noticed a strange sensation/hearing change.  Not sure how to describe it, but sort of like I went up a mountain and my ears haven't popped yet, or my head is underwater or full of Jell-o.  Lower pitched sounds seem especially distorted/loud/resonant, kind of uncomfortably so.  It seems like it's taking me slightly longer to process what my husband is saying, maybe because it's sort of blurry sounding, or maybe because I'm just distracted by the vibration of it.  My own voice makes my head feel like it's buzzing, if that makes any sense.  I just read that Bell's palsy is a possible side effect of the Moderna vaccine; I don't have any facial paralysis or anything like that, but the Wikipedia article I was looking at mentioned "hyperacusis" and "dysacusis", which seem like what I'm experiencing.  Maybe totally unrelated?  (Also maybe totally unrelated: my father had a brief episode of Bell's palsy when he was 40.  Treated with prednisone.  Never recurred that I'm aware of.)  The other symptoms (soreness at injection site, fever/chills, aches) all stopped by Thursday night, but the hearing weirdness (a clinical term) has persisted--this is Saturday night.  Maybe it's a little better, or maybe I'm just getting used to it, but my head/ears are still not feeling normal.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Approx a week after I got second (final) vaccine my left eye began twitching. I paid no attention to it. On March 5th I woke up with double vision. It went away within an hour and I worked a full 8 hour day. By the time I got home it was full blown double vision. I attended urgent care who diagnosed me "Cranial Nerve 4 palsy." I was recommended to see an opthomologist who confirmed this. I wasn't comfortable with this and asked to see a neurologist who also said cranial nerve 4 palsy. I asked for a brain MRI as I felt something more was going on. The MRI shown no abnormal findings (done 3/11/2021). On 3/16/2021 I woke up with a drooping eyelid of left eye. I immediately called opthomologist who suggested a diagnosis of Myesthenia Gravis. This was confirmed by neurologist on 3/23/2021. I am now on Prednisone and Mestinon. My next plan is to see a MG Specialist at A referral has been sent to them by my neurologist.
LAB_DATA: Antibody blood tests which are pending. 3/23
HISTORY: Exercise induced asthma  BP findings were 6 months old. Sudden onset.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Customer arrived at Appointment for COVID vaccine around 4:15 pm on 03/26/2021. After filling out VAR, customer was then brought into vaccinating room and vaccinated around 4:30pm. Vaccinating technician asked me to come in and look at his arm as he had a knot come up on the area that he was vaccinated immediately after his vaccination. I had seen this reaction before and told him not to worry and to put ice on it later when he went home. About 5 min later as we were talking customer became pale, he was a little nauseous, he did not feel right and became diaphoretic, but was breathing fine. Technician asked me to get him a cold cloth, and I brought 2, she placed one on his neck and I placed one on his head. I instructed patient to put his head between his knees as he was sitting, but he was concentrating on his breathing as we were talking to him. Customer did not lose consciousnessand his breathing remained stable. I stepped back into the pharmacy to continue work while the tecnician stayed with him to continue to monitor him. After a little bit I stepped back into the vaccination room and relieved the technician so that she could continue to vaccinate. His temperature was 98 and his color was looking better. He began to talk to me more, so we carried on a conversation as I continued to place cold compresses on his head and neck. After about another 15 or 20 min another tecnician came in with a fan to circulate air and  relieved me as I needed to check another prescription. The FE manager was talking to him and checking his BP the technician said that the customer told her that he had not been feeling well for the past 2 weeks and that he had seen a doctor and they were running some tests to figure out why he was feeling the way he was. The customer did not state any of this on his VAR nor tell us before his vaccine. He also told the technician checking him in that he had a little to eat that day as he was on site with his job most of the day. The FE manager opened the door from the vaccination room and advised us the he called EMS to pick up Patient as his BP was 80/40 and his pulse was 42. EMS came soon after and transported Patient at around 5:30pm. No medications were administered to the customer at the pharmacy by any Pharmacy employee. When I arrived at work this am (03/27/21) there was a voicemail from 9:39 pm the previous night and it was Patient's wife stating that her husband was in the hospital and that they would be here at some point to pick up the truck. She wanted to let us know so that the truck would not be towed.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: sweating; Pain in arm; Fever; Chest pain (left side); No bowel movement-watery; Labored breathing; Over sleeping; Passed out; Chills; Dizziness; Headache; A spontaneous report was received from a consumer concerning a 70-years-old female patient who received Moderna COVID 19 vaccine and experienced pain in arm, dizziness, major chest pain (left side), pain in shoulder, neck, headache, no bowel movement-watery, chills, labored breathing, passed out, over sleeping, no urine, sweating, fever and sore throat.  The patient's medical history included congestive heart failure, high blood pressure and gout and had 3 heart attacks in lifetime. No relevant concomitant medications were reported.  On 12 Mar 2021, prior to the onset of the event, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (lot/batch number: 031A21A) intramuscularly for COVID-19 prophylaxis.  On 12 Mar 2021, the patient experienced headache and dizziness. On 13 Mar 2021, the patient experienced pain in arm, major chest pain (left side), pain in shoulder, neck, no bowel movement-watery, chills, labored breathing, passed out, over sleeping, no urine, sweating, fever and sore throat. Treatment for the event included nitroglycerin and paracetamol.  Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was not reported.  The outcome of the event dizziness was resolved on 12 Mar 2021. The outcome of the events chills, fever and headache was resolved on 14 Mar 2021. The outcome of the events pain in arm, major chest pain (left side), pain in shoulder, neck, no bowel movement-watery, labored breathing, passed out, over sleeping, no urine, sweating and sore throat was resolved on 15 Mar 2021.; Reporter's Comments: This case concerns a 70 Y/O F with a serious unexpected loss of consciousness and NS unexpected dizziness, chest pain, dyspnea, gastrointestinal motility disorder, hypersomnia, hyperhidrosis, and expected pain in extremity, pyrexia, chills, headache.  Event onset Day 1 after first dose mRNA-1273. Events resolved. Based on current available information and temporal association between use of the product and the start date of the event, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.
CUR_ILL: Blood pressure; Congestive heart failure (Patient had 3 heart attacks in lifetime.); Gout

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Seizures; Swelling in left arm where she got the vaccine; A spontaneous report was received from a pharmacist concerning a female patient of an unknown age who received Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine (mRNA-1273) and experienced seizures and swelling in left arm where she got the vaccine.  The patient's medical history was not provided. No relevant concomitant medications were reported.  On 12 Mar 2021, prior to the onset of the events, the patient received their second of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (batch number: 044A21A) intramuscularly in the left arm for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.   On 12 Mar 2021, the patient experienced swelling in left arm where she got the vaccine. On 15 Mar 2021, the patient had medically significant event of seizures and was hospitalized for less than 24 hours. No treatment information was provided.  The patient received both scheduled doses of mRNA-1273 prior to the events, therefore action taken with the drug in response to the events was not applicable.  The outcome of the event swelling in left arm where she got the vaccine was resolved on 12 Mar 2021. The outcome of the event seizure was resolved on 15 Mar 2021.; Reporter's Comments: Based on the current available information which shows a temporal association between the use of the mRNA-1273 and the start date of the reported events and excluding any other etiology, a causal relationship with the events cannot be excluded. Injection site swelling is consistent with the safety profile of the product
HISTORY: Medical History/Concurrent Conditions: No adverse event (No medical history reported)

SYMPTOM_TEXT: complete hearing loss in my left ear for about four hours/ noticed but undocumented hearing loss; headache; chills; hangover feeling; incredibly loud ringing in left ear/ intermittent throughout the day, lasting for several hours at some points/ constant dull ringing/ tinnitus/ ringing in both ears; The initial safety information received was reporting only non-serious adverse drug reactions. Upon receipt of follow-up information on 22Mar2021, this case now contains serious adverse reaction. Information processed together.  This is a spontaneous report from a contactable Other Health Professional (patient). A 30-year-old female patient (not pregnant) received the first dose of BNT162B2 (PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 VACCINE, batch/lot EN6201) via intramuscular at left deltoid on 19Feb2021 at 14:30 (30-year-old at time of vaccination), at single dose, for COVID-19 immunization. The patient's medical history included bipolar disorder, ADHD, depression, and low Vit D. The patient had no COVID prior vaccination. There were no known allergies. Concomitant medications included lamotrigine (LAMICTAL) from 2016 and ongoing for bipolar, sertraline hydrochloride (ZOLOFT) from 2020 and ongoing for Bipolar, amfetamine/dexamfetamine (reported as amphetamine/dextroamphetamine salt extended) from 2015 and ongoing for ADHD and depression, Vitamin D3 from 2020 and ongoing for low Vit D, and cyanocobalamin (VITAMIN B12). The patient did not receive other vaccine in four weeks. Facility type was school or student health clinic; vaccine was administered at military facility. On 20Feb2021 at 21:00, patient had the normal headache, chills, "hangover feeling" in addition to an incredibly loud ringing in her left ear after her first dose. The ringing was intermittent throughout the day, lasting for several hours at some points. The intensity of it has subsided but there seems to be a constant dull ringing in her left ear now. She also had some weird effects with her medications the two days following her first dose. Not entirely sure if they're related but her medication seemed to be ineffective on Saturday and have little effect on Sunday. Severe tinnitus began around 10:00 (as reported) following her first vaccination, resulting in complete hearing loss in her left ear for about four hours. After that the severe ringing was intermittent for about five more hours. She now has ringing in both ears since, with noticed but undocumented hearing loss. There were no further complications after the second dose. The second dose (batch/lot number EN6205) was received via Intramuscular at left deltoid on 12Mar2021 at 14:00. The adverse events did not result in emergency room visit or physician office visit. The patient did not test COVID post vaccination. No therapeutic measures were taken as a result of the events. The outcome of tinnitus was not recovered; outcome of other events was recovered with sequel.
OTHER_MEDS: LAMICTAL; ZOLOFT; AMFETAMINE;DEXAMFETAMINE; VITAMIN D3; VITAMIN B12 [CYANOCOBALAMIN]
HISTORY: Medical History/Concurrent Conditions: ADHD; Bipolar disorder; Depression; Vitamin D low

SYMPTOM_TEXT: fuzzy; confused; got really hot; dizzy; flash of heat; This is a spontaneous report from a contactable nurse (patient). A 57-year-old female patient received the first dose of BNT162B2 (PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 VACCINE, lot number EN6207) intramuscular in the right arm on 10Mar2021 (time the vaccination was given: 08:45-09:00) at a single dose for COVID-19 immunization. There were no medical history and no concomitant medications. The patient had no family medical history. There were no additional vaccines administered on same date of the Pfizer suspect. No previous immunization with the Pfizer vaccine considered as suspect. No prior vaccinations within 4 weeks. Adverse event (AE) following prior vaccinations were noted as none (never had a reaction to a vaccine before). It was reported that the patient would like to know if she should receive her second dose of the Pfizer BioNTech COVID-19 vaccine based on the side effects she experienced after receiving her first dose yesterday. She already has an appointment scheduled for second dose. She waited in store 10 minutes after receiving it and felt fine. On the drive home, she felt a little fuzzy or confused and then got really hot and felt a little dizzy, but that went away within 15 minutes. It was further stated that within 15 minutes of getting the vaccine on 10Mar2021, she "got kind of fuzzy" (felt fuzzy) and first confused 09:10, then felt hot and then dizzy 09:15; these events were assessed as serious medically significant. Additionally, she experienced a "flash of heat that went through her body" on 10Mar2021 which went away within 10 minutes. No ER or physician's office required.  She felt like if she just got some water, she would be fine. No test was done. The feeling of confusion was what lasted the most and the dizziness did not last very long. The outcome of the events was recovered on 10Mar2021. The events felt fuzzy, confused, hot and dizzy was related to BNT162B2 per reporter.; Sender's Comments: Based on temporal association, a possible contributory role of BNT162B2 cannot be excluded for reported events fuzzy, confused, feeling hot and dizzy. The impact of this report on the benefit/risk profile of the Pfizer product is evaluated as part of Pfizer procedures for safety evaluation, including the review and analysis of aggregate data for adverse events. Any safety concern identified as part of this review, as well as any appropriate action in response, will be promptly notified to Regulatory Authorities, Ethics Committees and Investigators, as appropriate.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: feel like I have a chest cold.; feeling like I had the flu; trouble breathing; fatigue; throat has been a little sore; cough; feel like allergies all flared environmental and food; nausea; felt horrible; This is a spontaneous report from a contactable consumer, the patient. A 48-year-old non-pregnant female patient received the first dose of BNT162B2 (PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 MRNA VACCINE; Lot number: ENG199), via an unspecified route of administration in the left arm on 04Mar2021 at 17:30 (at the age of 48-years-old) as a single dose for COVID-19 immunization. Medical history included rheumatoid arthritis, vestibular migraines, allergies to all tree nuts, sunflower oil 25 very high, milk and egg whites, environmental allergy, the patient was recently vegan due to an anaphylactic attack. The patient was not diagnosed with COVID-19 prior to vaccination. Concomitant medications included hydroxychloroquine, varenicline tartrate (CHANTIX), escitalopram oxalate (LEXAPRO), lisdexamfetamine mesilate (VYVANSE), metronidazole (TRIAM). There was no other vaccine administered within 4 weeks of the vaccination. On 05Mar2021 at 00:00, the patient woke up feeling like she had the flu. She had trouble breathing and felt like she had a chest cold. She felt fatigue and horrible. This reminded her of how she felt when she had strep throat. Her throat had been a little sore, she had a cough and nausea. She also felt like her environmental and food allergies flared. The patient was not treated for the events. Since the vaccination, the patient had not been tested for COVID-19. The clinical outcome of "feel like I have a chest cold", "feeling like I had the flu", trouble breathing, fatigue, throat has been a little sore, cough, "feel like allergies all flared environmental and food", nausea and felt horrible was resolving.
HISTORY: Medical History/Concurrent Conditions: Allergy to nuts; Anaphylactic reaction; Egg allergy; Environmental allergy; Milk allergy; Oil allergy; Rheumatoid arthritis; Vegan; Vestibular migraine

heart attack; pass blood clots in his urine; nauseous; really tired; knocked him on his butt/did not get out of bed, did not do anything for 2 weeks; couldn't stay awake/ slept for two weeks; couldn't eat anything; the sight or smell of food made him gag; bruise on his arm about the size of a half dollar where he got the shot; This is a spontaneous report from a contactable consumer.  A 69-year-old male patient received the first dose of BNT162B2 (PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 VACCINE; solution for injection, Lot Number: EN6201), via an unspecified route of administration, administered on the right arm at the age of 69 years, on 18Feb2021 16:00 at a single dose for COVID-19 immunisation. Medical history included known for a history of heart disease, stage 4 kidney failure and polycystic disease. He had been bleeding from the kidneys for a week prior to receiving the vaccine, heart attack and cholesterol. He stated he needs some reassurance and added he has Stage 4 kidney failure with polycystic disease. He already consulted with his heart doctor and kidney doctor and they say get the vaccine. He mentioned that every now and then he gets blood from a cyst rupture. On the day of the first shot he was having a little bit of bleeding in his urine. Concomitant medications included acetylsalicylic acid, ascorbic acid (ASPIRIN [ACETYLSALICYLIC ACID;ASCORBIC ACID]) taken for cardiac disorder; atorvastatin (ATORVASTATIN) taken for blood cholesterol abnormal; amlodipine (AMLODIPINE) taken for blood pressure abnormal and multivitamins. The first shot knocked him on his butt. He slept for two weeks then he started to pass blood clots in his urine. He read that the vaccine can cause clotting and he doesn't know if that might have caused the clots right after the shot. He just needs someone to hold his hand about getting the second shot. He has to leave in a couple of hours to get it. He was asking do we see a pattern where people have had a bad first reaction with the first shot and they don't have a bad a reaction the second time around. He clarified he received the first dose of the Pfizer COVID 19 vaccine on 18Feb2021 at 1600 in the right arm. He was fine until Saturday (20Feb2021) when he woke up nauseous; really tired; could not get out of bed; and then really didn't do anything for two weeks. He added he couldn't stay awake even sitting up in his chair. He couldn't eat anything because the sight or smell of food made him gag, even in the grocery store. He added he also noticed he started to get the blood clots in his urine the second day after the shot (20Feb2021). On 19Feb2021, he mentioned he had a bruise on his arm about the size of a half dollar where he got the shot and he usually does not bruise. He stated he felt like he had all the symptoms of COVID. All of these symptoms lasted two weeks. When he finally felt better the only thing he wanted to eat was a burger and fries. He is still bleeding but it is not clotting anymore. The clots only lasted about a week. He also thought he was having a heart attack, but was too tired to go to the hospital. After speaking to his physician/specialist, they encouraged him to go ahead and get the 2nd dose. The patient  would like to know whether the benefits outweigh the risks for him to receive the 2nd dose of the Pfizer covid vaccine based on his medical history. The patient would like to know whether one dose of the Pfizer covid vaccine provides some protection. The patient was asking whether he might die from receiving the 2nd dose of the Pfizer covid vaccine. The outcome of the events heart attack was unknown; events bruise on his arm about the size of a half dollar where he got the shot and blood clot in urine was recovered on 27Feb2021 while other events were recovered on 06Mar2021.
HISTORY: Medical History/Concurrent Conditions: Blood cholesterol abnormal; Blood in urine; Blood pressure abnormal; Cyst rupture; Heart disorder (history of heart disease); Kidney failure (stage 4 kidney failure); Polycystic kidney (polycystic disease, Polycystic kidney); Renal haemorrhage

Patient was administered vaccine and told to wait the 15 minute monitoring period. After about 4 minutes, I heard her say "I'm not feeling right." I went to where she was sitting and asked "are you ok?" and had her take some slow, deep breaths. I then saw her eyes roll back and she lost consciousness. Thankfully, I was there and grabbed her as she toppled from the chair. I told the staff to call 911 and supported her neck and body in the chair. I could tell she was breathing and she was sweating profusely. I held her and spoke to her, and after about 15 seconds, she began to come out of it. After about a minute she was alert and orientated again.  I had her slowly sip a little water. The EMTs arrived in about 5 minutes and the assessed her vitals. She indicated that this was the first time anything like this had happened to her. They advised that since she had fainted, she should go to the hospital for observation, but she declined, stated that she felt fine at that point. Since she was driving, I insisted that she remain another one-half hour before leaving. During that time she drank more water and alternately sat and walked around the pharmacy. She did indicate that she had drank a protein shake that morning, but not eaten. I advised her to in the future, tell her doctor and/or any immunizer about the event. She left, stating that she was feeling fine, and I called her several hours later to make sure that she had indeed gotten home ok. She again said that she felt fine.

I took pictures of my hives as well if anyone needs them.  At this point I made a telehealth appointment with my doctor. She looked at them and said they were mild, and I should be ok to take the second shot. She prescribed me an epipen to take with me just in case. She told me to take Claritin during the day and benadryl at night.  Since then most of the hives have gone away, but I am still waking up with one or two new ones every day, in different places. Today there is a hive on my right thigh and left knee, both small but itchy.   The hives are small, the size of a quarter or smaller. They are red, initially they look swollen and are really itchy. Then they flatten out to be red and kind of splotchy, not as round as when they first form. They are super itchy. Then they fade away very slowly. I still have marks from the first hives on March 12.  I've never had allergies or hives like this in my life before the vaccine.

The day after the shot, I had itching all over my body. I took Zyrtec and Benadryl to help control that. On the third day (March 8) I developed a rash on the back of my neck. It was a pink color and raised. After a week with no improvement, I went to my doctor (March 16). They prescribed prednisone for me to use if the rash worsened. We decided I would not fill the prescription right away because the Zyrtec and the Benadryl were controlling the itching and the rash was not spreading. By March 20,  the rash spread to the front of my neck and ears, so I started taking the prednisone. The prednisone was effective and the rash seemed to disappear. I finished the prednisone on March 26. On March 27, I woke up with the rash all over my neck, back, chest and arms. It was a much more raised and a much darker red. I sent pictures and called my doctor?s on-call number. Because the rash was so bad all over my neck, they wanted me to go to an urgent care or ER to be checked out. I went to the ER and was prescribed a stronger steroid (40 mg). Today (March 28) is my second day with that medication. The rash is still here but maybe a bit lighter. I don?t think I?ll be comfortable getting the second vaccine. My kids have anaphylactic food allergies, so now I?m thinking they should receive the vaccine either. I?d love some advice on this.

On 28 March 2021, Patient received his Janssen Covid-19 vaccine. The vaccine was administered in the LEFT shoulder, lateral deltoid muscle. Time of vaccine administration (12:01pm), the needle separated from the syringe. This caused the patient to only receive half of the 0.5mL vaccine volume.  The injection site was then covered with a band aid, and the patient was informed to wait 15 minutes before leaving the clinic. He was informed to return to clinic in one hour as shot administration had stopped. CDC guidelines were reverenced regarding incomplete Covid-19 vaccine administration. It was decided since the true volume administered could not be verified, the patient would receive another complete 0.5mL Janssen vaccine. At 2:01pm, patient received 0.5mL of Janssen Covid-19 vaccine in the RIGHT shoulder, lateral deltoid muscle. He then waited another 15 minutes following the vaccine administration. He did not report any adverse reaction to the vaccine and was cleared to leave the clinic. He was informed of common side effects of the vaccine. No other adverse event took place. The event to report is that patient received approximately 0.75mL of the Janssen vaccine as the first dose was incomplete. No other adverse event took place aside from the mishap administering the first vaccine.  He did not experience any health concerns from receiving the vaccine.

Sunday, thirst, chills and fever were gone, but I had an intermittent headache, sore arm where shot was given and my other arm!, also muscle aches and tiredness. By Monday, I had muscle aches,  tiredness and light-headedness; Tuesday I had slight nausea and headache a short while, but mainly tiredness. Wednesday, I still had soreness where shot was given, tiredness and light-headedness, but otherwise was feeling better.  I canceled plans Thursday involving heavy physical labor (native plant restoration)  just to rest a bit more. Basically, I had a bouquet of symptoms over several days - grateful not to have had all at once and can only imagine how bad coronavirus must be.

Sometimes it is mild 2 or 3/10; sometimes medium 5 or 6/10 at times it has been at least 9/10. It can feel good one minute and then be very painful without any movement or other change in position within 10 minutes. Sometimes responds well to NSAIDs, sometimes it does not. SYMPTOM_TEXT: How the Vaccine affected my Sleep Apnea  Diagnosed: Severe Sleep Apnea Obstructive & Central 2 � years ago with 55 events/hour Machine: BiPap ResMed AirCurve 10 ASV with Memory Foam Full Mask  Vaccine: Moderna  My first shot had little effect with minimal soreness in my arm and a slight headache. The second shot had much more effect on me. I was very active the day of the second shot and the next day. Then it hit me hard. One of the greatest benefits of my Bi-Pap is how it works on my depression and anxiety. I was really sick with headaches, fever, no energy, body aches and really being in bed all day. Unfortunately the depression hit me also. It is like a lead blanket (like the dentist uses for x-rays) over you as you ball up in bed as your mind thinks why do I exist and how to end it with more feeling of anxiety. It really felt like I would die but knew from my experience that it may pass. Luckily it did but it took 10 days before feeling alive again. I also wondered why my events/hour increased at this time and concluded that the vaccine affected my Sleep Apnea.  My Data:  30 day average: 6.34 events/hour  90 day average: 4.64 events/hour 365 day average 3.89events/hour  As you see I have a good events/hour average but it has really increased this month since I got the Vaccine. Here are my numbers.  First Vaccine February 2021 18th  3.0 events/hour (day of shot) 19th  8.6 events/hour 20th  5.2 events/hour 21st  3.1 events/hour 22nd 2.2 events/hour  Second Vaccine March 2021 18th 4 events/hour (day of shot) 19th 6.8 events/hour 20th 15.5 events/hour 21st  5 events/hour 22nd 7.1 events/hour 23rd  5.3 events/hour 24th  5.2 events/hour 25th  6.9 events/hour 26th  3.6 events/hour 27th  2.9 events/hour

Within five minutes of receiving the first dose of the Moderna vaccine,  I started to feel slight pain in the injection site (my arm) reminiscent of a bruise. An hour later, I started to feel tired and weak, and the soreness in my arm worsened slightly. The pain on a scale of 1-10 was a 3.  45 minutes later, I experienced stiffness in my neck and upper back, though that isn't unusual for me. I also started to feel nauseous and cold at that time, but the nausea subsided within an hour.  The severity of these symptoms stayed the same the rest of the evening. I went to bed at midnight, and woke the next morning at 8am. My arm where I had received the shot felt much more sore and painful, especially when I move it, and mainly when any pressure is applied to the area. I was woken by pain in my arm when I payed on that side of my body. The pain is now a 4, but a 7 when pressure is applied. It is now 12:30 pm.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: At 2-8-21 at approximately 1:00pm I recieved my 2nd shot. At 5:00am on 2-9-21, I woke up experiencing an extreme headache, nausea, body aches, and severe chest pain. I checked my heartrate with a PulseOximeter and found it to be elevated at 105-115. I called out of work and rested in bed for the day. On 2-10-21 most of my symptoms had subsided however the chest pain persisted through 2-11-21. On 2-11-21 at 2:00pm, I visited the Urgent Care. While there, the provider ran an ECG, Chest X-Ray, and bloodwork. Test results showed Troponin levels in my blood had reached critical levels of 7.72ng/ml. I was immediately transported to the ER at the Hospital, where upon arrival they did an EKG and bloodwork. I was then admitted and seen by a cardiologist, who ordered an CT Angiogram, more bloodwork, and an Echocardiogram. After I was admitted, my mother contact the nurses station to check on me and asked what was wrong. She was then told the hospital was treating me for an NSTEMI and Myocarditis. This resulted in a 3 day hospital stay where the results of the tests showed there was nothing wrong with my heart other than the increased Troponin levels. It should be noted that I have had ZERO previous cardiac issues, or any other significant health issues. I was discharged from the hospital with lower but still elevated Troponin levels, and told to follow up with my primary care doctor. I had no health issues and felt fine until I had my second dose of the Covid-19 vaccine.  I have copies of my hospital records detailing all of this.
LAB_DATA: Elevated Troponin levels of 9585.8 ng/L in my blood. EKG, Echocargiogram, and CT Angiogram showed normal results

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I received my vaccine at 10:15 am on March 18, 2021, and was fine until 6 pm that evening.After eating dinner, I took my omesartan and pravastatin, as usual, and within 10 minutes, my heart rate became erratic.  I have tachycardia (SVT) but control it with atenolol.  I went to the ER at where I had an EKG, ches xray, and blood work.  My heartbeat reached 143.  While waiting on the test results, I noticed a rash forming below both my knees.  The ER doctor returned with the news that all tests came back normal with no accounting for the rapid heart beat other than the Pfizer vaccine.  He checked the rash saying it was likely another reaction from the vaccine.  He gave me medication to reduce my heart rate, prescribed hydrocortisone for the "rash" and released me.  By the next morning, my heart rate was back to normal but the "rash" had spread all over both legs.  On Saturday, March 20,, 2021, I went to a medical clinic to see if I could Triamcinolone Acetonide on the rash as the hydrocortisone wasn't helping.  The NP identified the rash as petechiae and prescribed Triamcinolone.  She could not prescribe an oral steroid xplaining that not enough info is known about the Covid vaccines and possible interactions with steroids.  I then followed up on Monday, March 22, 2021, with my PCP who said I had a bad case of petechiae and did more blood work to rule out vasculitis.  The day before getting the vaccine, I competed a 7-day course of the antibiotic Nitrofurintoin for a UTI and suggested to her that perhaps I  had a delayed reaction to it.  However, she ruled that out saying I would likely have had a reaction before the day after completing the medication.  She called me back the next evening on Tuesday, March 23 advising that all blood work came back negative, that the Pfizer vaccine is  likely the cause of the petechiae, and that I should probably not get the 2nd vaccine.  I asked her if she thought I would be okay getting the Johnson & Johnson vaccine and she said yes, if they will give it to you.  I could not get directed to anyone to answer that question,  but I need to know.  Can you help  me?
LAB_DATA: 03/18/2021 EKG, chest xray and blood work related to heart 03/22/2021 Blood work to test for vasculitis due to severe petechiae fully on both legs
OTHER_MEDS: Olmesartan, pravastatin, atenolol, Vitamins D3 and B12, 81 mg. aspirin, loratadine
CUR_ILL: UTI previous week prior to vaccine; last nitrofurintoin taken the morning of the day before vaccine.
HISTORY: tachycardia, high BP, high cholesterol, kidney diseas, osteoarthritis, vaginal & bladder prolapse, degenerative disc disease
